<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/1897a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Treasury</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Owing to the present disturbances in Mexico City, I have the honor to
                            request that you send telegraphic instructions to the appropriate
                            customs officials to withhold shipments of arms or munitions of war
                            consigned to Mexico City or any point in the State of Mexico, whether
                            already excepted by the President or not, until I shall again
                            communicate with you. The President is being informed of this
                            request.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>